    %h1 Lennard-Jones potential
    #chart
    #description
      %h2 About the Lennard-Jones potential graph
      %p
        The Lennard-Jones potential is a simple model describing the forces between
        a pair of neutral atoms or molecules.
      %p
        In the graph above you can change the force as a function of distance by either
        changing the depth of the potential well by dragging epsilon up and down or changing
        the zero point for the potential by dragging sigma left and right.
      %h2 References:
      %p
        %a{:href => "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lennard-Jones_potential"} Wikipedia: Lennard-Jones Potential
